statement.tex:
\text{Is th function defined by}\\
f(x) = \begin{cases} 
         x, if\, x \leq 1 \\
         5, if \,x\gt 1 
         \end{cases} \\
\text{Countinuous at x=0? At x=1?At x=2?}

step.reason:
\text{For a function to be continuous at a\\
point it's limits on either sides should be equal\\
to the valuse of f(x) at that point}

step.tex:
\begin{align}
    \lim_{x\to 1^-}f(x) &=1 \\
    \lim_{x\to 1^+}f(x) &=5 \\
    f(1) &= 1
\end{align}
\\ \text{Hence, f(x) is discontinuous at x=1.}\\

\begin{align}
    \lim_{x\to 1^-}f(x) &=1 \\
    \lim_{x\to 1^+}f(x) &=1 \\
    f(1) &= 1
\end{align}
\\ \text{Hence, f(x) is continuous at x=1.}\\
\therefore \text{ it is continuous at all x.}
